    <item>
      <title>Getting Started</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1314/01-introduction/01-getting-started/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1314/01-introduction/01-getting-started/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In this lesson you will install the robot simulator and verify that&#xA;your Python environment is ready.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You need Python 3.10 or newer. Check your version:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;python3 --version&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;callout callout-tip&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-title&#34;&gt;Tip&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;    If you have multiple Python versions installed, make sure &lt;code&gt;python3&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;points to 3.10+. Use &lt;code&gt;pyenv&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;conda&lt;/code&gt; to manage versions.&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;install-the-simulator&#34;&gt;Install the Simulator&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install robot-explorer-sim&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;callout callout-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-title&#34;&gt;Info&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;    The simulator opens a window using &lt;code&gt;pygame&lt;/code&gt;. On headless servers you&#xA;will need a virtual display such as &lt;code&gt;Xvfb&lt;/code&gt;.&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;run-your-first-simulation&#34;&gt;Run Your First Simulation&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-python&#34; data-lang=&#34;python&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; robot_sim &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; World, Robot&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;world &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; World(width&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;20&lt;/span&gt;, height&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;20&lt;/span&gt;)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;bot   &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; Robot(world, start&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;))&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;bot&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;move_forward(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;bot&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;turn_right()&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;bot&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;move_forward(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;world&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;render()&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;callout callout-warning&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-title&#34;&gt;Warning&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;    Always call &lt;code&gt;world.render()&lt;/code&gt; at the end of your script, or the&#xA;simulator window will close immediately.&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;instructor-guide-section&#34; style=&#34;display:none;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;h2 id=&#34;instructor-notes&#34;&gt;Instructor Notes&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Common issues&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Movement and Coordinates</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1314/01-introduction/02-movement-and-coordinates/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1314/01-introduction/02-movement-and-coordinates/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The robot lives on a 2-D grid. Understanding the coordinate system is&#xA;essential before we add sensors or decision-making.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-grid&#34;&gt;The Grid&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Each cell on the grid is identified by &lt;code&gt;(column, row)&lt;/code&gt; — &lt;code&gt;(0, 0)&lt;/code&gt; is the&#xA;&lt;strong&gt;top-left&lt;/strong&gt; corner. Column numbers increase to the right; row numbers&#xA;increase downward.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;(0,0)  (1,0)  (2,0) ...&#xA;(0,1)  (1,1)  (2,1) ...&#xA;(0,2)  (1,2)  (2,2) ...&#xA;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;callout callout-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-title&#34;&gt;Info&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;    This is the standard screen coordinate system used by most 2-D game&#xA;engines. It is the &lt;em&gt;opposite&lt;/em&gt; of the mathematical convention where &lt;code&gt;y&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;increases upward.&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;robot-headings&#34;&gt;Robot Headings&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The robot always faces one of four cardinal directions:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
